----------------------------------------------------------------------
Data sources
----------------------------------------------------------------------

The bundled ruling database (data/judgments.db) is derived from public
court records:

  · Polish court judgments (SR, SO, SA, SN) via SAOS — System Analizy
    Orzeczeń Sądowych, maintained by CeON / ICM University of Warsaw.
    Polish judicial decisions are excluded from copyright protection
    under art. 4 of the Polish Act on Copyright and Related Rights
    (ustawa o prawie autorskim i prawach pokrewnych).

  · CJEU judgments via CELLAR (Publications Office of the European
    Union), reusable under Commission Decision 2011/833/EU. NOTE: the
    CJEU pipeline is gated behind the SENTENTIM_ENABLE_CJEU=1
    environment variable and is not currently exercised by the
    published corpus (roadmap v0.5).

sententim does NOT redistribute the full text of judgments. Each row
contains only deterministically-extracted facts (signature, court,
date, outcome class, legal-basis citations) plus a SHA-256 of the
source text and a link back to the public source URL.

